- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): Although the paper does not explicitly mention computational geometry, the concept of clique-width is closely related to graph decompositions, which are often studied in computational geometry. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the b-Coloring problem on graphs of constant clique-width, which is a topic in computational complexity. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): Although the paper does not explicitly mention game theory, graph coloring problems are often studied in the context of game theory, where the colors represent different players.
